CSS rules to make styling work like you expect:    *, *:before, *:after {
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

I appreciate this post!  I was hoping you would add an inline CSS style sheet to take care of the broken defaults.  I only remember one off the top of my head, the rule for monospace font size.  You need something like:   code, pre, tt, kbd, samp {
     font-family: monospace, monospace;
   }

But I vaguely remember there are other broken CSS defaults for links, img tags, and other stuff.  An HTML 5 boilerplate guide should include that too, but I don't know of any that do.
